name: Earth Day
summary: Earth Day, celebrated annually on April 22nd, is a global event focused on raising awareness about environmental protection and promoting responsible actions. It has been instrumental in driving legislation such as the Clean Air Act and Clean Water Act, leading to significant improvements in environmental quality. Earth Day also fosters education and behavior change through campaigns like "green muscle memory" and climate education. Companies and organizations participate by offering discounts on eco-friendly products, hosting events, and launching initiatives to highlight the importance of environmental conservation. While Earth Day focuses on the well-being of the planet, it ultimately emphasizes the interdependence between human health and the environment. It encourages individuals to connect with nature, adopt sustainable practices, and work towards a healthier and more sustainable future for all.

Tickets for the event are on sale now, and some screenings of the show will be free to attend. The town of Bowral is undergoing a transformation to match the Regency era setting of "Bridgerton," with businesses and buildings decorating their storefronts and staff dressing in period costumes. The event is expected to provide a boost to the local economy, as well as generate excitement for the new season of the show.
